    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 1,
        "summary": "The fear of the Lord is the beginning of knowledge\u2014If sinners entice you, do not consent\u2014Those who hearken to wisdom will dwell safely.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The proverbs of Solomon the son of David, king of Israel;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 4:32; Prov. 10:1; 25:1.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To know wisdom and instruction; to perceive the words of understanding;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To receive the instruction of wisdom, justice, and judgment, and equity;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Edification; Teachable.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To give subtilty to the simple, to the young man knowledge and discretion.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 8:5.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A wise man will hear, and will increase learning; and a man of understanding shall attain unto wise counsels:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Education; Learn.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "To understand a proverb, and the interpretation; the words of the wise, and their dark sayings.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0riddles.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The fear of the Lord is the beginning of knowledge: but fools despise wisdom and instruction.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Discernment, Spiritual; Knowledge.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wisdom.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 76
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Problem-Solving.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "My son, hear the instruction of thy father, and forsake not the law of thy mother:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Education.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Children, Duties of.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For they shall be an ornament of grace unto thy head, and chains about thy neck.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 25:12.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 3:22.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "My son, if sinners entice thee, consent thou not.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Temptation.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 1:1 (1\u20132); Eph. 5:11 (8\u201313).",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If they say, Come with us, let us lay wait for blood, let us lurk privily for the innocent without cause:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0ambush, lie in wait.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 812
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let us swallow them up alive as the grave; and whole, as those that go down into the pit:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 124:3.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 28:1.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "We shall find all precious substance, we shall fill our houses with spoil:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Cast in thy lot among us; let us all have one purse:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "My son, walk not thou in the way with them; refrain thy foot from their path:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Abstain; Self-Mastery.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For their feet run to evil, and make haste to shed blood.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 59:7; 2\u00a0Ne. 19:17; D&C 64:16.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Surely in vain the net is spread in the sight of any bird.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they lay wait for their own blood; they lurk privily for their own lives.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "So are the ways of every one that is greedy of gain; which taketh away the life of the owners thereof.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Selfishness.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Wisdom crieth without; she uttereth her voice in the streets:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "She crieth in the chief place of concourse, in the openings of the gates: in the city she uttereth her words, saying,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 117
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "How long, ye simple ones, will ye love simplicity? and the scorners delight in their scorning, and fools hate knowledge?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Malice.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 93
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hate.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 109
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Knowledge.",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 119
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Turn you at my reproof: behold, I will pour out my spirit unto you, I will make known my words unto you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 42:1; D&C 19:38; 95:4.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Because I have called, and ye refused; I have stretched out my hand, and no man regarded;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Disobedience.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But ye have set at nought all my counsel, and would none of my reproof:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 4:21.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Counsel.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I also will laugh at your calamity; I will mock when your fear cometh;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When your fear cometh as desolation, and your destruction cometh as a whirlwind; when distress and anguish cometh upon you.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then shall they call upon me, but I will not answer; they shall seek me early, but they shall not find me:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Access to.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Judg. 10:14 (13\u201314); 2\u00a0Kgs. 3:13; Job 27:9; Ps. 66:18; Jer. 2:28 (26\u201337); D&C 101:7.",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For that they hated knowledge, and did not choose the fear of the Lord:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Agency.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They would none of my counsel: they despised all my reproof.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reproof.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore shall they eat of the fruit of their own way, and be filled with their own devices.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 6:19 (18\u201325).",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the turning away of the simple shall slay them, and the prosperity of fools shall destroy them.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But whoso hearkeneth unto me shall dwell safely, and shall be quiet from fear of evil.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}